â€¢â€¢Â°We can build Forms by using the form element <form>, with an <input>, a <label>, and a submit <button>.Â°Â°Â°

Â°Â°A "<form>" element consists of a start tag <form>, with optional attributes that define  the start tag, and the end tag </form>.Â°Â°Â°

Â°Â°Â° Here is a example of a script that will capture the processes running on a <form>.
Â°Â°Example
<form action="https://dailyinvestors.github.io/Tasks">
...
</form>
âš ï¸This makes a backend request to handle and process the data.
