â€¢â€¢Always provide <text> to help your clients with input.â€¢â€¢

â€¢â€¢ Use <textarea> for longer strings of text.â€¢â€¢
<textarea> is resizable. We can edit, or stop through CSS { resize: none, resize: verticalâ€¢â€¢â€¢

â€¢â€¢ <type=checkbox> or <select> for Options.â€¢â€¢

â€¢â€¢Wecan use the <accent-color> CSS property to change the color of  each form: including: <input type="range">.â€¢â€¢â€¢

â€¢â€¢ We can use <input> with <data list> to also display Optionsâ€¢â€¢

â€¢â€¢Use <input> with type="hidden" to create and hide objectsâ€¢â€¢â€¢

â€¢â€¢â€¢To enable your users to upload and submit files: We can use <input> with type="file"
Example:
<main>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <form>
       <div>
        <label for="photo">Photo</label>
        <input type="file" id="photo" name="photo">
      </div>
      <button>Upload</button>
    </form>
  </div>
</main>

CSS Value:
label {
  display: block;
  margin-top: 1rem;
}

button {
  margin-top: 2rem;
}

ğŸš¨ <input type="file"> can also allow your clients to upload multiple files.
